  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="pipeline">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Production lifecycle</div><h2>Six durable stages, not one opaque generation call.</h2></div>
      <p>Every expensive boundary follows a persisted checkpoint. A failed stage can resume from approved work instead of recreating the production.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-pipeline arch-glass">
      <% @pipeline_stages.each do |number, title, description| %>
        <article class="arch-stage">
          <div class="arch-stage__number"><%= number %></div><h3><%= title %></h3><p><%= description %></p>
          <div class="arch-stage__state">Persisted checkpoint</div>
        </article>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="topology">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">System topology</div><h2>Control plane, intelligence plane and media plane.</h2></div>
      <p>Rails owns state and policy. Qwen and HappyHorse provide bounded intelligence and synthesis. FFmpeg deterministically assembles the approved result.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-topology arch-glass">
      <div class="arch-lane">
        <div class="arch-lane__title">Interface</div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="amber"><strong>Projects UI</strong><span>Prompt, forecast approval, direction and production history.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node"><strong>Review Workspace</strong><span>Script, canonical assets, storyboard, QA and recovery controls.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="teal"><strong>ActionCable</strong><span>Live checkpoint, render and outcome events.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-lane">
        <div class="arch-lane__title">Rails control plane</div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="amber"><strong>ProjectsController</strong><span>Validates intent, enforces Full Control choices and issues one-shot authorizations.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="teal"><strong>ShowrunnerAgent</strong><span>Pre-production orchestration with monotonic, resumable checkpoints.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="red"><strong>ProduceDramaJob</strong><span>Single-render claim, synthesis, final QA, accounting and explicit outcome.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node"><strong>Sidekiq + Redis</strong><span>Asynchronous jobs without duplicate planning/render claims.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-lane">
        <div class="arch-lane__title">Consistency intelligence</div>
        <div class="arch-node"><strong>ScriptConsistencyValidator</strong><span>Repairs safe ambiguities and blocks hard narrative contradictions.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node"><strong>ProductionBible + ContinuityPlanner</strong><span>Canonical entities, scale, physics, agency and per-shot state.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="teal"><strong>VisualConsistencyEvaluator</strong><span>Storyboard vision QA against narrative and QA-only references.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="red"><strong>VideoConsistencyEvaluator</strong><span>Temporal and visual audit of generated clips with bounded repair.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-lane">
        <div class="arch-lane__title">Media + providers</div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="amber"><strong>QwenRouter</strong><span>Structured narrative and multimodal QA with a shared token ledger.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="red"><strong>HappyHorseClient</strong><span>T2I, I2V, R2V and T2V provider boundary.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node" data-tone="teal"><strong>CanonicalMediaStore</strong><span>Content-addressed, durable copies of validated visual references.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-node"><strong>AudioDirector + FFmpeg</strong><span>Required narration/music resolution and deterministic final assembly.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="consistency">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Consistency contract</div><h2>Visual invariants are hard gates.</h2></div>
      <p>Cinematic style may vary. Identity, canonical geometry and story state may not. A high average never compensates for one failed critical dimension.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-contract-grid">
      <% labels = { "identity_score" => ["Identity", "Face, body proportions, wardrobe and distinctive features."], "prop_score" => ["Canonical objects", "Color, material, dimensions, design and recurring-object fidelity."], "scale_score" => ["Relative scale", "Same-class geometry and scene-relative dimensionality."], "physics_plausibility_score" => ["Physics", "Attachment, contact, motion, causality and permitted agency."] } %>
      <% labels.each do |key, (title, description)| %>
        <article class="arch-contract arch-glass"><div class="arch-score">≥ <%= @visual_dimension_thresholds.fetch(key) %></div><h3><%= title %></h3><p><%= description %></p></article>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-callout arch-glass" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <strong>Overall storyboard threshold: <%= @visual_pass_threshold %>/100 — with every dimension passing its own hard minimum.</strong>
      <p>Calibration sheets, grids and technical labels are isolated as QA-only evidence. They are excluded from narrative image inputs and final frames.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-boundary">
      <div class="arch-boundary__column arch-glass"><h3>Locked across scenes</h3><ul><li>Character and human identity</li><li>Body and object proportions</li><li>Wardrobe, colors and materials</li><li>Recurring props and location geometry</li><li>Attachment and physical constraints</li><li>Initial/final state continuity</li></ul></div>
      <div class="arch-boundary__divider">Creative boundary</div>
      <div class="arch-boundary__column arch-glass"><h3>Directed creatively</h3><ul><li>Composition and lens selection</li><li>Camera movement and coverage</li><li>Lighting and color treatment</li><li>Editing rhythm and transitions</li><li>Music and voice treatment</li><li>Performance within canonical agency</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="modes">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Production authority</div><h2>Automatic resolves; Full Control obeys.</h2></div>
      <p>Neither mode silently weakens narrative or asset contracts. They differ in who resolves creative defaults and whether repairs happen automatically.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-mode-grid">
      <article class="arch-mode arch-glass"><div class="arch-mode__tag">Automatic</div><h3>Policy-driven completion</h3><p>The app selects safe defaults and works toward a complete assembled film.</p><ul><li>Resolves unspecified direction and audio choices</li><li>Performs one bounded automatic visual repair</li><li>Reuses approved clips and checkpoints</li><li>Stops only on non-overridable contract failures</li></ul></article>
      <article class="arch-mode arch-mode--control arch-glass"><div class="arch-mode__tag">Full Control</div><h3>Explicit producer authority</h3><p>The app requires choices and executes the producer's requested action.</p><ul><li>No hidden cinematic defaults</li><li>Regenerates only the requested asset or frame</li><li>No automatic clip repair unless explicitly requested</li><li>Can accept visual-only risk for one exact render contract</li></ul></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="recovery">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Cost and failure containment</div><h2>Recovery is monotonic and scoped.</h2></div>
      <p>The system preserves successful work, exposes the blocker and prevents an unbounded regenerate–audit loop.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-recovery arch-glass">
      <div class="arch-recovery__step"><small>Before create</small><strong>Token forecast</strong><span>Predicts likely range, excess and repair reserve from script complexity and history.</span></div>
      <div class="arch-recovery__step"><small>Before provider</small><strong>Budget gate</strong><span>Requires forecast approval or a one-shot “spend beyond limit” authorization.</span></div>
      <div class="arch-recovery__step"><small>After each stage</small><strong>Checkpoint</strong><span>Persists screenplay, assets, storyboard and actual ledger usage.</span></div>
      <div class="arch-recovery__step"><small>On QA failure</small><strong>Targeted repair</strong><span>Regenerates only failed frames or clips; measured passes are reused.</span></div>
      <div class="arch-recovery__step"><small>On final failure</small><strong>Recoverable cut</strong><span>Preserves an assembled cut for explicit acceptance without another paid render.</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-callout arch-glass" style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>Durable reference rule</strong><p>Signed provider URLs are copied while valid into <code>/public/generated/projects/:id/media/:sha256.ext</code>. UI, QA and video generation fall back to that exact validated file instead of purchasing a replacement. Local files become data URIs only at the provider boundary and are never stored as base64 in the database.</p></div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="components">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Core implementation map</div><h2>Components and their single responsibility.</h2></div>
      <p>The production manifest is the contract shared by these services; no provider is allowed to become the source of truth.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-component-grid">
      <% components = [
        ["ProductionTokenPredictor", "Forecast", "Estimates narrative, asset, storyboard, QA, video and repair token demand."],
        ["ProductionModePolicy", "Authority", "Resolves Automatic defaults and rejects incomplete Full Control configurations."],
        ["PreproductionCheckpoint", "Persistence", "Makes planning resumable and records cost after every durable stage."],
        ["AssetProfiler", "Canonical assets", "Extracts source-faithful characters, humans, props, locations, identity and scale."],
        ["ProductionBible", "Visual contract", "Separates narrative references from technical QA evidence and defines invariants."],
        ["ScreenplayPlanner", "Timing", "Normalizes scene/shot timing and creates the authoritative edit decision list."],
        ["StoryboardPromptCompiler", "Shot semantics", "Compiles one atomic visible action, state transition and camera contract per shot."],
        ["ContinuityPlatePlanner", "Spatial anchor", "Creates a reusable master composition for scale and location continuity."],
        ["CanonicalMediaStore", "Durable media", "Validates, hashes, deduplicates and persists approved visual references."],
        ["ConsistencyOverridePolicy", "Scoped override", "Binds producer risk acceptance to the exact storyboard/render digest."],
        ["VideoSynth", "Clip strategy", "Chooses keyframe I2V, character R2V or T2V and reuses provider tasks safely."],
        ["AudioDirector + Editor", "Delivery", "Resolves audio requirements and assembles a clean film without debug overlays."]
      ] %>
      <% components.each do |name, role, description| %><article class="arch-component arch-glass"><code><%= name %></code><h3><%= role %></h3><p><%= description %></p></article><% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="arch-section" id="data">
    <div class="arch-section__head">
      <div><div class="arch-eyebrow">Persistence model</div><h2>The manifest is an auditable production ledger.</h2></div>
      <p>PostgreSQL stores the declarative contract and runtime outcomes. Binary references remain content-addressed on disk; provider task IDs remain recoverable.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="arch-data-grid">
      <article class="arch-data-card arch-glass"><h3>Project manifest</h3><div class="arch-data-list">
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>screenplay</code><span>Scenes, atomic shots, initial/final states, continuity bindings and timing.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>assets</code><span>Canonical profiles plus remote and durable reference roles.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>production_bible</code><span>Entity invariants, scale anchors, physics, agency and negative constraints.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>consistency_report</code><span>Structural, script, source-fidelity and storyboard vision results.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>video_consistency_report</code><span>Per-clip final QA, repair attempts and explicit risk outcome.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>render_runtime</code><span>Version, job claim, start/finish, terminal outcome and actionable error.</span></div>
      </div></article>
      <article class="arch-data-card arch-glass"><h3>Operational safeguards</h3><div class="arch-data-list">
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>SHA-256 media</code><span>Byte-identical deduplication and stable UI refresh.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>20 MB cap</code><span>Bounded download and provider payload size.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>Image signatures</code><span>PNG, JPEG and WebP payload verification.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>SSRF guard</code><span>Rejects private, loopback and link-local media hosts.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>One-shot grants</code><span>Token overrun and visual-risk authority are consumed by one operation.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-data-row"><code>Idempotent claims</code><span>Stale or duplicate planning/render jobs cannot reopen completed work.</span></div>
      </div></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="arch-footer"><span>SHOWRUNNER · consistency-first film orchestration</span><span>Architecture runtime: <%= @architecture_version %></span></footer>
</div>
